Package: grass
Type: Package
Title: Context-Conditioned Reporting for Binary Rater Reliability
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Austin", "Semmel", email = "runfast031@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Rachel", "Gidaro", role = "aut"))
Description: Generates a four-field Report Card for binary inter-rater
    agreement from an N x k rating matrix. Each candidate coefficient
    (Cohen's kappa, PABAK, Gwet's AC1, Fleiss kappa, Krippendorff alpha,
    observed ICC) is positioned on a calibrated reference surface
    conditioned on the study's rater count, sample size, and prevalence,
    yielding a surface-position percentile, a four-band qualitative label,
    and a Neyman-Pearson-motivated delta-hat stability flag from
    cross-coefficient spread. When the panel is divergent, per-rater sensitivity and
    specificity are recovered from a Dawid-Skene latent-class fit
    (Hui-Walter bounds at k = 2). The package implements the GRASS
    submodule of the MEADOW framework (Semmel 202X).
